# MTC Game Development Rules

## Doc Sync Rule — runs on EVERY commit

### Trigger
When committing any file in js/ or css/ — always run this checklist BEFORE writing commit message.

### Step 1: Scan what changed
List all modified files. For each file, note:
- New classes / renamed classes
- New global variables / window.* exports
- New skills / weapons / enemies / bosses
- Changed property names (e.g. cooldown keys, stat names)
- Changed inheritance or file structure
- Removed classes or features

### Step 2: Update PROJECT_OVERVIEW.md
Update ONLY sections affected by the changes above:
- File Structure table — if files added/moved/removed
- Character Quick-Stats table 🔴 — if config.js balance changed
- Auto Rework section — if AutoPlayer.js or config auto stats changed
- Wave Events table — if WaveManager.js wave logic changed
- MTC Room section — if map.js bounds/features changed
- Energy Cost table — if new skill costs added
- Muzzle Offset table — if weapons.js offsets changed
- Recent Changes — always add [NEXT VERSION] entry summarizing the patch
- Status line version — leave as [NEXT VERSION]

DO NOT rewrite stable sections (Architecture, Workflow, AI Roles) unless explicitly instructed.

### Step 3: Update SKILL.md
Update ONLY if the commit changes any of these:
- Class names or constructor names → Section 2 (Class Name Map)
- Inheritance chain → Section 3
- AI file load order or API method names → Section 4
- Property rules (vx/vy, stats.moveSpeed, etc.) → Section 5
- Global variable patterns → Section 6
- Domain singleton behavior → Section 7
- Rendering layer order or variable declaration rules → Section 8
- effects.js exports → Section 9
- Poom routing rules → Section 10
- Heat tier values or Stand Pull cooldown keys → Section 11
- config.js BALANCE structure → Section 12
- New file created → Section 13 (checklist)
- Version number in status line → Section header

If nothing in the commit touches the above — SKIP SKILL.md update entirely.

### Step 4: Bump version (existing rule)
sw.js → CHANGELOG.md → PROJECT_OVERVIEW.md status line
Use format [NEXT VERSION] in PROJECT_OVERVIEW and SKILL.md — bump actual number only in sw.js + CHANGELOG.

### Step 5: Write commit message
Format: "vX.X.X — <summary>\n\n<bullet list of changes>"

