## Commit & Push Workflow

### Priority Sequence:
1. **PROJECT_OVERVIEW.md** (FIRST - PRIORITY #1)
2. Update sw.js (CACHE_NAME version)
3. Update CHANGELOG.md
4. Update other documentation files
5. Commit & push

### Reason for Priority:
- PROJECT_OVERVIEW.md serves as the "AI Assistant Handbook" for understanding project context
- New AI sessions read this file first to understand the codebase
- Outdated PROJECT_OVERVIEW.md leads to incorrect assumptions and wasted time
- Other documentation files are secondary to project context understanding

### Commit Message Format:
- **Standard Format**: "vX.X.X: [Type] [Short Description] - [Detailed Explanation]"
- **Types**: Fix, Feature, Enhancement, Performance, Documentation, Refactor
- **Examples**:
  - "v3.4.17: Fixed malformed CSS selector in index.html - corrected invalid Unicode characters in feature list that was causing display issues"
  - "v3.3.3: Fixed kills display - added kills param to showGameOver() to properly show player statistics on game over screen"

